{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/falls-risk-assessment/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"0e9e44f9-c35d-5a6b-9e5b-78dfbe3f2f0f","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 4ea0603d-cdee-4f6b-93f8-a7f20188d038 --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field 4ea0603d-cdee-4f6b-93f8-a7f20188d038 -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 2596f04a-5324-452b-95fc-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field 0534ed21-fae1-40ad-8272-a7f20188d038 --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 0534ed21-fae1-40ad-8272-a7f20188d038 --><!-- begin field 1fd81d53-e7ee-4d33-b0f1-a7f20188d038 --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field 1fd81d53-e7ee-4d33-b0f1-a7f20188d038 --><!-- begin field 2b59a36e-4851-4c77-8196-a7f20188d038 --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 2b59a36e-4851-4c77-8196-a7f20188d038 --><!-- begin field 5ad370fc-0069-4f58-b99a-a7f20188d038 --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 5ad370fc-0069-4f58-b99a-a7f20188d038 --><!-- begin field 55eeb1db-82b1-47a8-b5d3-a7f20188d038 --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field 55eeb1db-82b1-47a8-b5d3-a7f20188d038 --><!-- begin field 61ea39d1-86d7-4748-86e2-a7f20188d038 --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field 61ea39d1-86d7-4748-86e2-a7f20188d038 --><!-- end item 2596f04a-5324-452b-95fc-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"ec87421f-7ea3-508d-ba78-b50bdd43d3be","topicId":"984467a2-6284-4f25-bee5-6b2b114c7a25","topicName":"Falls - risk assessment","slug":"falls-risk-assessment","lastRevised":"Last revised in January 2019","chapters":[{"id":"f7133733-e8a8-50b4-bc9e-7c7ba69a4c89","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"e0f0a6f6-15c7-5f54-8d83-39498083ebbe","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"d7606aa8-482e-59a5-875e-4ea9e8822ffb","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"4c51223c-3e20-557c-bb60-804b7d270b72","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"b1003ba1-7b3d-5063-98e7-82df1ba2747f","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"d9dc05de-7d7f-58cb-b4b9-28a486b286c3","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"5d07f83f-e9db-52b3-adc8-9aefa0325f29","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"7c2374a2-9bde-51a6-81f3-96e22df36fad","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"4a8a6ffa-98db-5cb9-a735-fdb85cdd6f02","slug":"audit-criteria","fu